1 B. In the hearing on a petition under this act, the court shall
2 consider any evidence that the respondent believed in good faith
3 that the respondent's conduct was necessary to avoid imminent harm
4 to the child or respondent and any other evidence that may be
5 relevant to whether the respondent may be permitted to remove or
