4 An abduction prevention order remains in effect until the
5 earliest of the:
6 1. Time stated in the order;
7 2. Emancipation of the child;
8 3. Child attaining eighteen (18) years of age; or
9 4. Time the order is modified, revoked, vacated, or superseded
10 by a court with jurisdiction under Sections 551-201, 551-202, and
11 551-203 of Title 43 of the Oklahoma Statutes or other applicable
12 laws of this state.
13 SECTION 11. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 571-111 of Title 43, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 In applying and construing the Uniform Child Abduction
17 Prevention Act, consideration shall be given to the need to promote
18 uniformity of the law with respect to its subject matter among
19 states that enact it.
20 SECTION 12. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 571-112 of Title 43, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 This act modifies, limits, and supersedes the federal Electronic
24 Signatures in Global and National Commerce Act, Section 7001, et
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2081 SFLR Page 17
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 seq. of Title 15 of the United States Code, but does not modify,
2 limit, or supersede Section 101(c) of the act, 15 U.S.C., Section
3 7001(c), of that act or authorize electronic delivery of any of the
4 notices described in Section 103(b) of that act, 15 U.S.C., Section
5 7003(b).
6 SECTION 13. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
